//! # GIFTI-RS: Rust Implementation of GIFTI File Format
//!
//! This library provides a fast, safe Rust implementation of the GIFTI
//! (Geometry Format under the Neuroimaging Informatics Technology Initiative)
//! file format used in neuroimaging applications.
//!
//! GIFTI files are XML-based and contain surface data for brain imaging,
//! including vertices, triangles, and associated metadata.
//!
//! ## Features
//!
//! - **Fast XML parsing** with streaming support
//! - **Multiple encoding formats**: ASCII, Base64Binary, GZipBase64Binary, ExternalFileBinary
//! - **Comprehensive data types**: UINT8, INT32, UINT32, FLOAT32
//! - **Endianness handling**: BigEndian and LittleEndian support
//! - **Surface processing**: Triangle mesh operations and coordinate transformations
//! - **Memory efficient**: Zero-copy parsing where possible
//! - **Type-safe**: Leverages Rust's type system for data integrity
//!
//! ## Quick Start
//!
//! ```rust
//! use gifti::{read_gifti, write_gifti};
//!
//! // Read a GIFTI file
//! let gifti_data = read_gifti("surface.gii")?;
//! 
//! // Access the data
//! println!("Number of data arrays: {}", gifti_data.data_arrays.len());
//! 
//! // Write a GIFTI file
//! write_gifti(&gifti_data, "output.gii")?;
//! # Ok::<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>>(())
//! ```
//!
//! ## File Types Supported
//!
//! - **Surface files** (`.surf.gii`): Pointset and triangle data
//! - **Shape files** (`.shape.gii`): Scalar values per vertex
//! - **Time series** (`.time.gii`): Temporal data
//! - **Label files** (`.label.gii`): Categorical data with color tables
//! - **Compressed files** (`.gii.gz`): GZip compressed variants

#![doc(html_logo_url = "https://example.com/logo.png")]
#![doc(html_favicon_url = "https://example.com/favicon.ico")]
#![doc(html_root_url = "https://docs.rs/gifti/")]

pub mod core;
pub mod error;
pub mod io;
pub mod utils;

// Re-export main types and functions
pub use core::{
    DataArray, DataArrayAttributes, DataType, Encoding, Endianness, Gifti, Intent, MetaData,
};
pub use error::{GiftiError, Result};
pub use io::{read_gifti, write_gifti};
pub use utils::{convert_intent, is_gifti, surf_triangles};

// Version information
pub const VERSION: &str = env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION");
pub const GIFTI_VERSION: &str = "1.0";

